    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-09-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-09-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="217"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                <head>217. Telegram 6 from Geneva to Hong Kong<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d217fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                        611.95A251/9–2255. Confidential; Priority. Repeated to the Department of
                        State as telegram 760.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-09-22"
                            >September 22, 1955, noon</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d217-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d217-1"/>
                <p>6. Would appreciate any immediately available information whether nine jailed
                    Americans released from Communist China were informed by prison officials of
                    these negotiations or terms of agreed announcement before their release.
                        <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> has alleged remaining <pb
                        facs="0334" n="287" type="typeset" xml:id="pg_287"/> prisoners will be
                    informed agreed announcement by having newspapers read and if necessary
                    translated to them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Shillock</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
